-- South Korean Producer Prices Fall 2.6% in 8th Straight Decline
-- B y   C y n t h i a   K i m
-- 2013-06-17T21:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-17/south-korean-producer-prices-fall-2-6-in-8th-straight-decline.html
South Korean producer prices fell
2.6 percent in May from a year earlier, Bank of  Korea  says in an
e-mailed statement.
* The decline is at a slower pace after prices fell 2.8 percent
in April, the most since October 2009.
* Price drops in international raw materials including crude oil
contributed to the decline: statement  To contact the reporter on this story:
